25/01/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- In separate statements Thursday (January 24th), the junior allies in the government led by the Democratic Party (DP) reiterated calls for a cabinet reshuffle.
Vangjel Dule, leader of the Union of Human Rights Party, again urged Prime Minister Sali Berisha to review his team, insisting there is a need for ministerial changes in the next two to three months.
Fatmir Mediu, defence minister and chairman of the Republican Party, echoed the sentiment and suggests the ruling coalition partners hold a roundtable meeting to resolve the matter.
(GazetaShqiptare, Shekulli, Shqip - 25/01/08;
Balkanweb, Top-Channel - 24/01/08)
